# Split Licence Declaration

**Endorsement Marker:** T(h)reehouse +EC voyage repository. Local candidate framework — T(h)reehouse +EC stewardship. No external endorsement implied.

This repository follows the split licence architecture defined in the
T(h)reehouse +EC Corporate Design blueprint, Section 0.3
(`threehouse-plus-ec/cd-rules`, `blueprint-threehouse-CD.md`).

Consumers must check the licence of the specific layer they are using; no
single licence applies uniformly across the repository.

## Layer map

| Path | Layer | Licence | SPDX |
|------|-------|---------|------|
| `src/` | Infrastructure (code and tooling) | MIT | MIT |
| `requirements.txt` | Infrastructure | MIT | MIT |
| `.github/` | Infrastructure (CI configuration) | MIT | MIT |
| `docs/site/` | Infrastructure (static-site build scripts and stylesheet) | MIT | MIT |
| `docs/site/assets/` | Handbook (Model-B copies of CD assets) | MIT | MIT |
| `figures/` | Handbook (design / data assets) | MIT | MIT |
| `README.md` | Coastline (framework / method) | CC BY-SA 4.0 | CC-BY-SA-4.0 |
| `VOYAGE_PLAN.md` | Coastline | CC BY-SA 4.0 | CC-BY-SA-4.0 |
| `stages/` | Coastline (per-stage notes and protocols) | CC BY-SA 4.0 | CC-BY-SA-4.0 |
| `literature_search/` | Coastline (task cards, verifier/scout returns, reconciliation) | CC BY-SA 4.0 | CC-BY-SA-4.0 |
| `docs/` (non-`site/`) | Coastline | CC BY-SA 4.0 | CC-BY-SA-4.0 |
| `when-does-the-experiment-still-see.md` | Sail (authored essay); relicensed to CC BY-SA 4.0 by Harbourmaster decision (more permissive than default CD §0.3 Sail licence of CC BY-NC-SA 4.0) | CC BY-SA 4.0 | CC-BY-SA-4.0 |
| `archive/` | Preserves the licence in force at deprecation | — | — |

If a path is not listed, the enclosing folder's licence applies. When a folder
contains mixed content, the more restrictive licence applies unless individual
files carry their own header declarations.

Canonical licence texts:

- MIT — https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT
- CC BY-SA 4.0 — https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

